			<p>Weather permitting (and it's currently looking at bit iffy) the camera obscura will be set up at <a href="http://www.peopleandland.org.uk/wp/?p=1986">Highbury Park</a>, between Kings Heath and Stirchley, for their harvest celebration of five years of community gardening. It'll be a lovely afternoon regardless and well worth popping along to if you're local. </p>
<p>We expect to be set up in the middle of the park, at the play area up from the car park. If you follow the main path you'll find us! </p>
<p>As always check Twitter if you're coming to see us specially. If the weather looks really dodgy we may cancel. </p>
<p><a href="http://www.peopleandland.org.uk/wp/?p=1986"><img decoding="async" src="http://bhamobscura.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/11/2015/10/HarvestPoster-website.png" alt="HarvestPoster-website" width="605" height="855" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1572" srcset="http://www.ash10.com/bhamobscura/wp-content/uploads/sites/11/2015/10/HarvestPoster-website.png 605w, http://www.ash10.com/bhamobscura/wp-content/uploads/sites/11/2015/10/HarvestPoster-website-212x300.png 212w" sizes="(max-width: 605px) 100vw, 605px" /></a></p>

