		<div class="entry-content">

			<p>Our attention was drawn this week to the <a href="https://twitter.com/MadameGilflurt">MadameGilflurt</a> Twitter account who posts curious artworks from the 18th century and who had dug up this beauty, titled "The Camera Obscura" by Charles-Amédée-Philippe van Loo.</p>
<p><a href="https://twitter.com/MadameGilflurt/status/636184100009848832"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" src="http://bhamobscura.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/11/2015/08/MadameGilflurt_2015-Aug-25.jpg" alt="MadameGilflurt_2015-Aug-25" width="597" height="598" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1545" srcset="http://www.ash10.com/bhamobscura/wp-content/uploads/sites/11/2015/08/MadameGilflurt_2015-Aug-25.jpg 597w, http://www.ash10.com/bhamobscura/wp-content/uploads/sites/11/2015/08/MadameGilflurt_2015-Aug-25-150x150.jpg 150w, http://www.ash10.com/bhamobscura/wp-content/uploads/sites/11/2015/08/MadameGilflurt_2015-Aug-25-300x300.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 597px) 100vw, 597px" /></a></p>
<p>We got in touch and she used her archive-fu to dig up more for us, none of which we'd seen before, so here they are! </p>
<figure id="attachment_1546" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-1546" style="width: 699px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://www.rijksmuseum.nl/nl/collectie/RP-P-2006-36"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" src="http://bhamobscura.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/11/2015/08/Unknown-1.jpeg" alt="L&#039;optique&#039;, J.F. Cazenave, Louis-Léopold Boilly, ca. 1794" width="699" height="875" class="size-full wp-image-1546" srcset="http://www.ash10.com/bhamobscura/wp-content/uploads/sites/11/2015/08/Unknown-1.jpeg 699w, http://www.ash10.com/bhamobscura/wp-content/uploads/sites/11/2015/08/Unknown-1-240x300.jpeg 240w, http://www.ash10.com/bhamobscura/wp-content/uploads/sites/11/2015/08/Unknown-1-624x781.jpeg 624w" sizes="(max-width: 699px) 100vw, 699px" /></a><figcaption id="caption-attachment-1546" class="wp-caption-text">L'optique', J.F. Cazenave, Louis-Léopold Boilly, ca. 1794</figcaption></figure>
